<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Tooltip</h2>
        <p>
            Tooltips? More like Cooltips. But really though, tooltips are nifty for displaying extended information for a term or action on a page.
        </p>
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Basic Tooltip</h2>
        <p>By default, a tooltip appears below the defined term on hover.</p>
        <HighlightCode Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
                     Content="VGhlIDxUb29sdGlwIHRhYmluZGV4PSIxIiAgVGl0bGU9IkZhbmN5IHdvcmQgZm9yIGEgYmVldGxlLiI+c2NhcmFiYWV1czwvVG9vbHRpcD4gaHVuZyBxdWl0ZSBjbGVhciBvZiBhbnkgYnJhbmNoZXMsIGFuZCwgaWYgYWxsb3dlZCB0byBmYWxsLCB3b3VsZCBoYXZlIGZhbGxlbiBhdCBvdXIgZmVldC4=" />
        <p>
            The <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip tabindex="1"  Title="Fancy word for a beetle.">scarabaeus</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip> hung quite
            clear of any branches, and, if allowed to fall, would have fallen at our feet.
        </p>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Tooltip Top</h2>
        <p>
            To get a tip-top top tooltip (lol), just use <Code>@("<Tooltip>")</Code> element. The default position value of this balise is <code>top</code>
        </p>
        <HighlightCode Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" 
                     Content="VGhlIDxUb29sdGlwICB0YWJpbmRleD0iMiIgVGl0bGU9IkZhbmN5IHdvcmQgZm9yIGEgYmVldGxlLiI+c2NhcmFiYWV1czwvVG9vbHRpcD4gaHVuZyBxdWl0ZSBjbGVhciBvZiBhbnkgYnJhbmNoZXMsIGFuZCwgaWYgYWxsb3dlZCB0byBmYWxsLCB3b3VsZCBoYXZlIGZhbGxlbiBhdCBvdXIgZmVldC4=" />
        
        The <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip  tabindex="2" Title="Fancy word for a beetle.">scarabaeus</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip>
        hung quite clear of any branches, and, if allowed to fall, would have fallen at our feet.
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Tooltip clicking</h2>
        <p>
            By default, clicking on a tooltip will leave it open until you click somewhere else. However, you can disable that by
            adding <Code>DataClickOpen="false"</Code>
        </p>
        <HighlightCode Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
                     Content="dGhpcyA8VG9vbHRpcCAgdGFiaW5kZXg9IjIiIFRpdGxlPSJZb3Ugc2VlPyAgSSdtIG9wZW4hIj50b29sdGlwIHdpbGwgc3RheSBvcGVuPC9Ub29sdGlwPiB3aGlsZSA8VG9vbHRpcCBEYXRhQ2xpY2tPcGVuPSJmYWxzZSIgdGFiaW5kZXg9IjIiIFRpdGxlPSJJIGRvbid0IHN0YXkgb3BlbiI+IHRoaXMgb25lIHdpbGwgb25seSBiZSBvcGVuIHdoZW4gaG92ZXJlZDwvVG9vbHRpcD4=" />
        <p>
            this <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip  tabindex="2" Title="You see?  I'm open!">tooltip will stay open</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip> while <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip DataClickOpen="false" tabindex="2" Title="I don't stay open"> this one will only be open when hovered</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip>
        </p>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Tooltip Right and Left</h2>
        <p>You can also position the tooltips to the right and left of the word by seting the attribute position set it to <Code>right</Code> or <Code>left</Code> to the <Code>@("<Tooltip>")</Code> element.</p>
        <HighlightCode Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
                     Content="" />
        <p>
            When he was dressed he went down the hall into the <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip Position="right" tabindex="3" Title="Aligned on the right">kitchen</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip>.
            The table was almost hidden beneath all Dudley's birthday presents. It looked as though <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip Position="left" tabindex="4" Title="Aligned on the left">Dudley</OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Media.Tooltip>
            had gotten the new computer he wanted, not to mention the second television and the racing bike.
        </p>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>



